title: Taylor Swift, Ed Sheeran, The Weeknd lead AMA nominations
text:
CNN Leadership
Taylor Swift, Ed Sheeran, The Weeknd lead AMA nominations Updated 1645 GMT (2345 HKT) October 13, 2015 9 photos: 2015 American Music Awards nominees The 2015 American Music Awards will be held November 22. Leading all artists with six nominations is Taylor Swift. She's up for artist of the year, song of the year and favorite female artist, among others. Hide Caption 1 of 9 9 photos: 2015 American Music Awards nominees Ed Sheeran is up for five AMAs, including artist of the year and song of the year. Hide Caption 2 of 9 9 photos: 2015 American Music Awards nominees The Weeknd had a breakout year in 2015. His AMA nominations include artist of the year, song of the year and best new artist. Hide Caption 9 photos: 2015 American Music Awards nominees Nicki Minaj is another artist of the year nominee. She received three nominations in total. Hide Caption 9 photos: 2015 American Music Awards nominees Bruno Mars was nominated for his collaboration with producer and DJ Mark Ronson, "Uptown Funk." Hide Caption 5 of 9 9 photos: 2015 American Music Awards nominees Justin Bieber, rarely far from the spotlight, picked up an AMA nomination for his collaboration with Skrillex and Diplo, "Where Are U Now." Hide Caption 6 of 9 9 photos: 2015 American Music Awards nominees Sam Smith's three nominations are in the categories of artist of the year, favorite male artist (pop/rock) and favorite album (pop/rock). Hide Caption 7 of 9 9 photos: 2015 American Music Awards nominees Ariana Grande is up for artist of the year as well as favorite female artist (pop/rock). Hide Caption 8 of 9 9 photos: 2015 American Music Awards nominees Paul McCartney's unlikely collaboration with Kanye West and Rihanna, "FourFiveSeconds," is among the nominees for collaboration.
